PGP uses two encryption methods: the public-key part is RSA, the 
symmetric part is IDEA.  I'll let others to enlighten us on IDEA.  
(Are there any alternatives to Schneider's book and Lai's thesis?)  
(Note: Here "Lai" does NOT mean Albert Y.C. Lai. :)

Rivest, Shamir, Adleman, _A method for obtaining digital signatures 
and public key cryptosysterms_, Communications of the ACM, vol.21 
no.2, Feb 1978, pp120-126.

(And YES, I've glanced through it!)

> the technique used to encrypt a single message (producing only one
